      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Susan Ferrara is a Baum biographer and scholar. She is the author of <emph render="italic">The Family of the Wizard: the Baums of Syracuse</emph> and other books on L. Frank
            Baum and his work. She attended SUNY-Geneseo, the University of North Carolina at Chapel
            Hill, and the University of Maryland College Park. In the past she has worked as a
            writer/editor for ABC and currently does freelance research and writing.</p>
         <p>L. Frank Baum (1856-1919) is a beloved children's author, writer of <emph render="italic">The Wonderful Wizard of Oz</emph> and a plethora of other stories,
            poems, and scripts. The majority of this collection focuses on his niece, Cynthia Baum
            Tassini, for whom it is rumored the dedication in the <emph render="italic">The Emerald
               City of Oz </emph>("Dedicated to Her Royal Highness Cynthia II of Syracuse") could
            refer to.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Sue Ferrara Collection of Baum Research Material</emph> consists
            of research material gathered by Susan Ferrara during the course of her work, including
            correspondence and printed material.</p>
         <p><emph render="bold">Correspondence</emph> consists of incoming mail to Cynthia Baum
            Tassini.</p>
         <p><emph render="bold">Printed material</emph> contains clippings, books, and
            microfilm.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
         <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
         <p>Correspondence is arranged chronologically, with undated material or empty envelopes at
            the end. Printed material is single items, except for clippings, which are arranged
            chronologically with undated material at the end.</p>
      </arrangement>
